      "content": "Research how to implement Phase 17: Src/ audit — dead code, noise, context rot detection\n\n## Phase Goal\nAs a Hivemind project maintainer, I want to manually audit all src/ modules to identify dead code, noise, stub files, context rot, and test coverage gaps, producing a structured findings report for cleanup in Phase 18.\n\n## Context\nRead this file first: `.planning/phases/17-sync-boundary-definition-src-audit-and-cleanup/17-CONTEXT.md`\n\n## Key Decisions (from CONTEXT.md)\n- Manual review per module (not tool-based auto-detection)\n- All src/ modules to audit: shared/, features/, harness/ vs kernel/, cli/, config/, coordination/, hooks/, routing/, schema-kernel/, task-management/, tools/\n- Categories: dead code (0 imports), noise (stub/empty), context rot (stale patterns), test coverage gap\n- This is DISCOVERY ONLY — no file deletion or refactoring\n\n## What to investigate\n1. Current state of each src/ module — directory listing, file count, LOC\n2. Known issues: src/harness/ = src/kernel/ duplication, plugin.ts 447 LOC, messages-transform.ts dead\n3. Best practices for manual code audit (what patterns to look for)\n4. How to structure findings report for handoff to Phase 18\n5. What tooling can supplement manual review (grep patterns, import tracing)\n\n## Read these files:\n- `.planning/phases/17-sync-boundary-definition-src-audit-and-cleanup/17-CONTEXT.md`\n- `.planning/REQUIREMENTS.md`\n- `.planning/PROJECT.md`\n- `.planning/STATE.md`\n- `.planning/codebase/ARCHITECTURE.md`\n- `src/` directory structure (`ls -R src/ | head -100`)\n\n## Output\nWrite RESEARCH.md to: `.planning/phases/17-sync-boundary-definition-src-audit-and-cleanup/17-RESEARCH.md`\n\nCover:\n1. Module-by-module overview (current state, known issues)\n2. Audit methodology recommendations\n3. Findings report template/structure\n4. Risk assessment (what could go wrong)\n5. Effort estimate\n6. Handoff format for Phase 18",
