      "content": "## RESEARCH COMPLETE\n\n**Phase:** 17 — Sync Boundary Definition + Src/Audit\n**Confidence:** HIGH\n\n### Key Findings\n1. **Full module inventory completed** — 237 TypeScript files across 14 modules (~37,500 LOC total). Largest: `features/` (71 files, 13,473 LOC) and `coordination/` (31 files, 5,596 LOC).\n2. **8 pre-identified findings ready for confirmation** — including `harness/` + `kernel/` empty stubs, `plugin.ts` 493 LOC (target 100), `toggle-gates.ts` dead (0 imports), `runtime-detection/` stale (195 LOC unwired), `session-tracker/index.ts` 1035 LOC outlier, and 5 modules with zero test coverage (routing, task-management, sdk-delegation, command-delegation, steering-engine).\n3. **23 tools registered** in plugin.ts, all verified active via import tracing. **6 hook types** wired.\n4. **No test coverage for src/routing/**, **src/task-management/**, **coordination/command-delegation/**, **coordination/sdk-delegation/**, and **features/steering-engine/**.\n5. **Findings report template** provided with 8 pre-identified findings in the correct format for Phase 18 consumption.\n\n### File Created\n`.planning/phases/17-sync-boundary-definition-src-audit-and-cleanup/17-RESEARCH.md`\n\n### Confidence Assessment\n| Area | Level | Reason |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| Module Inventory | HIGH | All counts from live filesystem scan (2026-05-20) |\n| Import Analysis | HIGH | Verified via `grep -rn` across entire `src/` |\n| Dead Code | MEDIUM | ts-prune + grep provide candidates; manual reading needed for final verdict |\n| Architecture Compliance | MEDIUM | Patterns documented in ARCHITECTURE.md; manual reading needed to catch violations |\n\n### Open Questions\n1. `steering-engine/` (609 LOC) — dead or deferred? 0 imports from plugin.ts but may be wired via index.ts.\n2. `toggle-gates.ts` — truly dead or compile-time-only (TOG-01 marked DELIVERED in REQUREMENTS.md)?\n3. How to best split `session-tracker/index.ts` (1035 LOC, double the 500 cap)?\n\n### Ready for Planning\nResearch complete. Planner can now create PLAN.md for the audit execution. The recommended ordering is: `shared/ → config/ → routing/ → schema-kernel/ → tools/ → hooks/ → coordination/ → task-management/ → features/ → cli/ → sidecar/` — lowest risk first, highest risk last.",
